    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-12-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/2467</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Olds</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Colonel Olds</hi>: Very many thanks for your letter
                    of December 12th, notifying me of the negotiations now in progress at New York
                    between Mr. R. D. Hutchinson, Manager of the Aguila Company and representative
                    of the Mexican Estates Company in Mexico, and Mr. Frank Feuille, attorney in New
                    York for the Richmond Petroleum Company, relative to the latter’s application
                    for concessions covering lands in Mexico in which the Mexican Estates Company
                    owns a part interest. It would be most kind of you if you would inform me in due
                    course of the result of these negotiations.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Esme Howard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
